<p>When Haknir finally emerged from his cabin, the crew fell silent. He looked
frail, his voice raspy. But even so, he had a presence about him. As he looked
over his men, the most brutal murderers ever to ply the northern seas, not one
could meet his gaze. At last he sighed.</p>

<p>â€œYou wish to know who will by my successor, and how my share of the treasure
